blue
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:error, blunder, bloomer (unfortunate, unconscious) (esp. make a blue) (the infrequent verb blue (something), `to break, ruin (sthg)' seems formed on this noun, although it may be related to blue v1.), CCR suggests blow (sthg) with past tense blew it.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1953 16 M A32 Thames DHS 19 BLUE (BLOO) [make a mess]
